race.description: Ladbrokes Cup Eve Luncheon @ Country Club Hcp
race.comment: Tough race where most of the form is intertwined and includes five last start winners. SNOW EAGLE (5) isn't one of them but looks ready to win after three runs back. Tackled 1800m last time in open class and finished fourth. Extra trip is a plus and has the claim and inside draw. Expected to fire. JOHNNIE PINCH (1) was a BM68 winner last time over a mile after a string of solid runs over shorter trips. Has placed 3/4 this course and distance though and gets back out in journey now in winning form. Can measure up. CAPTAIN MORGAN (4) was a big winner over 2400m at Longford, scoring by four lengths. Tougher here but will be strong over the journey and can measure up again. JUDGE JENNI (7) got home hard to score a narrow win over 1650m on the synthetic at Devonport. Placed only try this trip and heading the right way. ZURICH (3) was a course and distance winner a few starts over where he beat a few of these including JUDGE JENNI. Second behind CAPTAIN MORGAN latest and has claims again.
